==背景==
继不具备法律约束力的《[[哥本哈根协议|哥本哈根协议]]》于2009年通过后，国际社会对本次会议的期望有所降低<ref>{{cite news |last=AP |first=Google News |title=As world warms, negotiators give talks another try |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5hA3Nfc02CbfSH2Iz5aR9AmCJjt3g |accessdate=2010-11-20 |newspaper=The Associated Press |date=2010-11-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101129042227/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5hA3Nfc02CbfSH2Iz5aR9AmCJjt3g |archivedate=2010-11-29 }}</ref>。2010年举办了四轮筹备谈判。前三轮分别于4月9日-11日、6月1日-11日、8月2日-6日在德国[[波恩|波恩]]举行。波恩谈判据报以失败告终<ref name="Vidal2010-08-06">{{cite news |last=Vidal |first=John |title=Climate talks in danger of unravelling as China and US clash |date=2010-08-06 |newspaper=[[卫报|卫报]] |location=London |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2010/aug/06/climate-talks-us-china-clash |accessdate=2010-10-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101012104127/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2010/aug/06/climate-talks-us-china-clash |archivedate=2010-10-12 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref name="Vidal2010-08-09">{{cite news | last = Vidal | first = John | title = UN climate talks are stuck in the mud | date = 2010-08-09 | newspaper = The Guardian | location = London | url = http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/aug/09/un-climate-change-cancun-mexico | accessdate = 2010-10-14 | archive-date = 2011-09-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110902163556/http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/aug/09/un-climate-change-cancun-mexico | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Vogel2010-09-08">{{cite web |last=Vogel |first=Toby |title=Climate talks going 'backwards', EU says |date=2010-09-08 |work=EuropeanVoice.com |publisher=[[经济学人|经济学人]] |url=http://www.europeanvoice.com/article/2010/08/climate-talks-going-backwards-eu-says/68691.aspx |accessdate=2010-10-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101029025013/http://www.europeanvoice.com/article/2010/08/climate-talks-going-backwards-eu-says/68691.aspx |archivedate=2010-10-29 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。第四轮谈判在中国[[天津|天津]]举行，会谈取得的进展甚微，中美两国甚至出现冲突<ref name="AP2010-10-09">{{cite news |title=U.S.-China Deadlock Dims Climate Talk Prospects |date=2010-10-09 |newspaper=New York Times |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/10/world/asia/10climate.html |accessdate=2010-10-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120624234438/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/10/world/asia/10climate.html |archivedate=2012-06-24 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref name="Watts2010-10-08">{{cite news |last=Watts |first=Jonathan |authorlink=Jonathan Watts |title=Climate tensions resurface as US clashes with China |date=2010-10-08 |url=http://www.smh.com.au/environment/climate-change/climate-tensions-resurface-as-us-clashes-with-china-20101007-169uh.html |newspaper=[[悉尼先驱晨报|悉尼先驱晨报]] |accessdate=2010-10-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101010025050/http://www.smh.com.au/environment/climate-change/climate-tensions-resurface-as-us-clashes-with-china-20101007-169uh.html |archivedate=2010-10-10 |deadurl=no }}</ref><ref name="Harrabin2010-10-09">{{cite news |last=Harrabin |first=Roger |authorlink=Roger Harrabin |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-11508913 |title=UN climate talks in China end without breakthrough |date=2010-10-09 |newspaper=BBC News |accessdate=2010-10-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101014045635/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-11508913 |archivedate=2010-10-14 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。2010年11月10日的塔拉瓦气候变化大会上，《安博宣言》被[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]、[[巴西|巴西]]、[[中国|中国]]、[[古巴|古巴]]、[[斐济|斐济]]、[[日本|日本]]、[[基里巴斯|基里巴斯]]、[[马尔代夫|马尔代夫]]、[[马绍尔群岛|马绍尔群岛]]、[[新西兰|新西兰]]、[[所罗门群岛|所罗门群岛]]和[[汤加|汤加]]采纳。该协议要求采取更多行动，预计在本次会议上提交。

==预期==
[[File:2010_UN_Climate_Talks.jpg|thumb]]
2010年8月，[[潘基文|潘基文]]表示，他怀疑成员国不会一次性达成一个“全球公认的全面协议”，而是会在日后逐步形成共识<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/10/science/earth/10nations.html?_r=1&ref=earth | title = U.N. Chief Recommends Small Steps on Climate | newspaper = New York Times | first = Neil | last = MacFarquhar | authorlink = Neil MacFarquhar | date = 2010-08-09 | accessdate = 2010-09-24 | archive-date = 2020-07-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200718235335/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/10/science/earth/10nations.html?_r=1&ref=earth | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

10月的天津对话后，联合国框架气候公约执行秘书[[克里斯蒂娜·菲格雷斯|克里斯蒂娜·菲格雷斯]]表示，“这个星期让我们朝着坎昆会议能够达成的一系列决策迈进了一步......它是世界目前社会和经济的最大转型。”

其他评论家对谈判表示积极的态度，称其为《坎昆协议》铺平道路<ref>{{cite news |last=Watts |first=Jonathan |authorlink=Jonathan Watts |title=Climate deal is closer, says UN envoy, despite China and US locking horns |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/oct/09/climate-talks-china-america-clash |newspaper=卫报 |accessdate=2010-10-10 |location=London |date=2010-10-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101011154720/http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/oct/09/climate-talks-china-america-clash |archivedate=2010-10-11 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

